<TITLE> US congratulates Bangladesh on successful polls </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 30 (bdnews24.com)The US has congratulated officials, candidates and voters on the success of Bangladesh's parliamentary elections, calling on the newly elected government and opposition to build a better future. "All Bangladeshis can take great pride in the success of these elections. The high voter turnout underscores the people's desire to see democracy restored as well to have a voice in their future," said a statement of the US State Department on Tuesday. "We also look forward to a continuation of the reforms that have enjoyed wide popular support." The US government congratulated the Bangladesh Election Commission "and the thousands of government officials involved in organising this successful election." It also lauded the conduct candidates and voters during the campaign and on Election Day. "Those elected must prepare to assume their roles as the representatives of all the people of Bangladesh while unsuccessful candidates should continue to participate in the political process," said the statement. "Whether in government or opposition, all political parties have an important role in helping to build a better future for Bangladesh," it added.
